 &UR; NETWORTH:  &LR;  Scholastic Inc. is printing 3.8 million copies of the
fourth installment in its wildly popular Harry Potter series.
That's a record first-run volume and it's soaking up a good chunk
of the nation's printing capacity. But that doesn't guarantee
everyone who wants the 752-page story about a teenage wizard will
magically get one.  &UR; COLUMN BY KATHLEEN PENDER &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; GROW:  &LR;   &LR;   &LR;  Business plan competitions have become the rage on
