<P>
   GERMANY-HITLER (Berlin) _ The presentation of a major German
prize to a historian who says Hitler was merely responding to
Bolshevism has created furor. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-HEALTH-CARE (Undated) _ In its first analysis of health
care systems around the world, the World Health Care Organization
has found that France provides the best overall care, followed by
Italy, Spain, Oman, Austria and Japan. By Philip J. Hilts. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-ROYALTY-BIRTHDAYS (Windsor, England) _ Five royal
birthdays are to be feted at a gala given by Queen Elizabeth II at
Windsor Castle on Wednesday night, but the celebrator who is the
hope for continuing generations of the beleaguered British monarchy
will be marking his 18 years less ceremoniously. Final exam studies
will keep Prince William in his Eton dormitory room, a 10-minute
walk from the largest joint royal birthday party in memory. But his
absence will hardly keep him and his official passing into
adulthood from being the center of royal-watching attention. A
journal by Warren Hoge.
