<SLUG> BC-AUTO-BRIEFS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     TOYOTA ROLLS OUT A RESTYLED COROLLA 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The restyled Toyota Corolla is the first 2001 model in the
company's lineup to arrive at dealerships nationwide.
</P>
<P>
   Deliveries of the car began late last month.
</P>
<P>
   Among the new features of this compact sedan are better fuel
economy, which the EPA estimates is 32 miles per gallon in the city
and 41 mpg on the highway for models with five-speed manual
transmission.
</P>
<P>
   Models with the three-speed automatic transmission are rated at
29 mpg city/33 highway, while the four-speed automatic gets 30 mpg
city/39 highway.
</P>
<P>
   This is Toyota's first car model with a safety release inside
the trunk to allow anyone who is accidentally locked in there to
open it and escape. Other automakers have begun installing these
releases, among them are Ford Motor Co., which put the releases in
the 2000 model Ford Taurus and Mercury Sable sedans.
</P>
<P>
   Exterior styling has been updated on the Corolla, including
aerodynamic multireflector halogen four-beam headlights,
chrome-plated front-end trim and a lowered front bumper.
</P>
<P>
   Also included are new tail lights and, on some versions,
color-keyed body side moldings.
</P>
<P>
   Interior enhancements are designed to give more convenience and
comfort. There are new seat fabrics, push-button air recirculation
controls and, for the uplevel LE model, a rearview mirror with
integrated map lights.
</P>
<P>
   Some models with automatic transmission have dual rear cup
holders and a larger center console with a larger armrest storage
compartment.
</P>
<P>
   The Corolla is Toyota's longtime compact sedan, which is second
from the bottom in price and size among the company's U.S. vehicle
lineup. The entry-level Toyota is now the Echo. Corollas are built
along with their clones, the Chevrolet Prizms, at the New United
Motor Manufacturing Inc. plant in Fremont, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   For more information about the new Corolla, check out Toyota's
Web site, www.toyota.com.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   CHRYSLER UNHAPPY WITH PT DEAL
</P>
<P>
   A New York dealer who marked the sticker prices of two PT
Cruisers up $10,000 each to sell the vehicles to the U.S.
government for crash testing was criticized by DaimlerChrysler
North America President Jim Holden for charging more than the
sticker price for the hot-selling cars, the trade weekly Automotive
News reported.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was an unfortunate mess with a salesman at a dealership
doing what he thought was cute,'' the magazine quoted Holden as
saying. ``He's embarrassed, the dealer's embarrassed, we're
embarrassed.''
</P>
<P>
   The dealer, in East Aurora, had found two of the PTs to sell to
the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration for front- and
side-impact crash tests. The test results are to be posted in early
July on the agency's Web site, www.nhtsa.gov.
</P>
<P>
   But the dealership was able to deliver only one of the PT
Cruisers it promised to the government. It seems the other one had
been promised to a retail customer, who turned down the
dealership's offer to split the extra $10,000 if the customer would
let the government have the car instead.
</P>
<P>
   The customer wanted the car instead of the $5,000, and the
government had to look elsewhere for its second PT, a spokesman for
the agency said. One was found at a so-far unnamed dealership in
the Midwest, but again, the government is being charged $10,000
over sticker for the car.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the first one delivered to the government has been
crashed and is headed for the junk heap. Results of the
frontal-impact test that the vehicle was used for will be posted on
the NHTSA Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Holden said he believes most Chrysler dealers are selling the PT
Cruisers at sticker price. Chrysler priced the vehicles under
$20,000 to create a mass market for them, and initial consumer
response has been overwhelming. Production has not come close to
matching customer demand; waits for the PT can be six months or
more.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   PORSCHE SUV NAMED FOR A PEPPER
</P>
<P>
   ``Cayenne'' will be the name of the new Porsche-built
sport-utility vehicle that will come with a high-performance engine
and a big-league price tag, Porsche of North America has announced.
</P>
<P>
   The vehicle, being developed jointly with Germany's Volkswagen,
is scheduled to go into production in 2002. Porsche hopes to sell
about 25,000 of the vehicles annually; it will be the first truck
product ever for Porsche, which has always been known in the United
States for its speedy (and expensive) little sports cars.
</P>
<P>
   Why Cayenne? The name is ``synonymous with spiciness and
adventure,'' the themes for the new SUV, Porsche officials said.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Contact G. Chambers Williams III by telephone at 210-250-3236
or by e-mail chambers(at)express-news.net)
</P>
</TEXT>
