<P>
   DEATH-GRAHAM _ AUSTIN, Texas _ A day before the controversial
execution of Gary Graham, a new poll in Texas shows that while a
majority of Texans, 57 percent, believe the state executes innocent
people, an overwhelming margin, 73 percent, continue to support
capital punishment. We compare the political sentiment in Texas
with the rest of the country and see how such high profile cases
are playing out for George W. Bush and his prospects of becoming
president. (Heath, Austin American-Statesman). 20-25. ETA: 6:30
p.m. EDT on the Budget Tool.
</P>
