<P>
   LABOR _ AFL-CIO President John Sweeney is planning to hold a
series of town hall meetings around the country to contrast the
records of Gov. George W. Bush and Vice President Gore on labor
issues. The publicity tour, designed to gin up support for Gore
among labor voters, comes as Gore confronts a revolt among
Teamsters and United Auto Workers unions over China trade
legislation. Green Party candidate Ralph Nader meets with Teamsters
president James Hoffa Thursday to seek the Teamsters' endorsement.
AFL-CIO town hall meetings scheduled for Philadelphia June 29 and
Atlanta in July. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
