alleging racial discrimination and sexual abuse. As reported
Tuesday in the Times. kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BURIAL -- Florida and several states approve a national
settlement over burial insurance. A seven-month state investigation
found that thousands of black Floridians paid up to a third more
for burial insurance than white policyholders. While insurers no
longer sell insurance, they still collect premiums. Insurance
Commissioner Bill Nelson said companies for decades preyed on poor,
unsophisticated blacks. Now they will be getting some of that money
back. (Ostrowski, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
