<P>
   BOOK-NOTES _ When Norris Church Mailer was writing her debut
novel, ``Windchill Summer,'' she didn't dare show it to her husband
Norman Mailer until it was already published. ``I had sent him a
love poem once, and he returned it to me marked up in red pencil,''
she says. This time Mailer was complimentary about the novel based
on Norris' life in Atkins, Ark., during the sixties as a pickle
packer. Other news: a look at Longstreet's success with best
sellers and the launching of a new publisher in Tennessee.
(O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 21.
