rasslin' than big-time freestyle and Greco Roman competition. Yet,
there figures to be one wrestler there who'll be cheered like he's
a lost member of the Von Erich clan, Brandon Slay. The Amarillo
native, who's seeded No. 1 in the 167-pound freestyle competition,
aims to become the first born and bred Texan to make the U.S.
Olympic wrestling team. If he can do that, he should have a serious
shot at winning a medal, even the gold one, at the 2000 Olympic
Games in Sydney. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman).
