to show it is sincere about wishing to tame runaway oil prices that
have pushed up energy bills in the West. The Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries agreed to lift output for 10 member
countries by a modest 3 percent increment of about 710,000 barrels
daily. (Summary from wires) By Edmund L. Andrews.
