<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUDIO-MINIS22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CD mini reviews
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray and Doug Hamilton
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  R&AMP;B
</P>
<P>
   ``Theonceandfuture''
</P>
<P>
   Jazzyfatnastees. Atlantic. 10 tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   Listening to the Jazzyfatnastees debut is something like lying
on a table, readying yourself for a massage. Atmospheric singers
coo out of the speakers, accompanied by a twinkling keyboard (``The
Wound'') or a sensual tug at a cello string (``Sail the Seas'').
Songs pass. And alas, the masseuse never comes. As pleasant and
melodious as Tracey Moore and Mercedes Martinez's vocals are _
particularly on the spare, '60s soul throwback ``Breakthrough'' _
and as lyrically purposeful as they try to be _ none of this nicely
produced CD ever really digs in and connects.
</P>
<P>
   _Sonia Murray
</P>
<P>
   Jazzyfatnastees will perform Saturday at Chocolate Soul at
Studio Central.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : More on Chocolate Soul:
www.chocolatesoul.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ROCK
</P>
<P>
   ``Set''
</P>
<P>
   Alex Chilton. Bar/None Records.
</P>
<P>
   12 tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   Maintaining what is likely one of the weakest work ethics in
popular music, cult icon Alex Chilton (formerly of the Box Tops and
Big Star) resurfaces every few years with another collection of
charmingingly tossed-off R&AMP;B covers. This ``Set,'' which includes
versions of ``Oogum Boogum'' and ``You's a Viper,'' was recorded in
a single February day in 1999. It sounds like it was the day after
a long night out. Chilton's famously flimsy voice is at its
thinnest, and the band takes what can only be called a hands-off
approach to tuning. If you heard some no-name group at a frat party
play like this, you'd probably leave. Coming from a bona fide rock
legend, though, it sounds ragged and right.
</P>
<P>
   _Doug Hamilton
</P>
<P>
   Alex Chilton will perform Friday at the Echo Lounge in East
Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : More on Alex Chilton and Bar/None Records
www
</P>
<P>
   .bar-none.com.
</P>
<P>
   Sonia Murray and Doug Hamilton write for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
