subcommittee votes on a Republican proposal to provide a private
prescription drug benefit for low-income Medicare beneficiaries.
President Clinton, who has an alternative plan, has called the GOP
proposal ``a fraud.'' (Lipman, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   GUN-CHECKS _ WASHINGTON _ The Senate introduced a bill Wednesday
to compensate states that perform their own background testing for
gun purchases. (O'Dell, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   LABOR _ AFL-CIO President John Sweeney is planning to hold a
series of town hall meetings around the country to contrast the
records of Gov. George W. Bush and Vice President Gore on labor
issues. The publicity tour, designed to gin up support for Gore
among labor voters, comes as Gore confronts a revolt among
Teamsters and United Auto Workers unions over China trade
legislation. Green Party candidate Ralph Nader meets with Teamsters
president James Hoffa Thursday to seek the Teamsters' endorsement.
AFL-CIO town hall meetings scheduled for Philadelphia June 29 and
Atlanta in July. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   FORT-STLOUIS-DIG _ VICTORIA, Texas _ The dirt near the water is
dark and sticky and thick with clues just a few inches deep.
Archaeologists rake the ground for ceramics, weapons, the bones of
soldiers buried before Texas was Texas. Nothing slips their
attention. Everything fetched from the clay of this old cattle
ranch is cleaned, dried, tagged and bagged in the hope that before
long, what is left of the first European colony in the state will
be dug from the banks of Garcitas Creek and preserved to explain
the rise and tragic fall of Fort St. Louis. (Robbins, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
