<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
story for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, June 22, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   LAKERS-PARADE (Los Angeles) _ More than 250,000 Lakers fans
ducked out of work and school to celebrate the new NBA champs, with
star Shaquille O'Neal promising another title next year. ``The
trophy is home where it belongs -- and we're going to get another
one next year. Can you dig it?'' O'Neal told the cheering crowd,
which stretched in front of the Staples Center. By Daily News staff
reporters. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   PARADE-VIOLENCE (Los Angeles) _ Despite heavy police security,
violence broke out in small pockets around the Staples Center. An
MTA bus was trashed and several cars were damaged, but there were
no injuries reported. Police arrested about 20 people an hour after
the parade ended. By Daily News staff reporters. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California state news files.)
