began 50 years ago Sunday and devastated the peninsula. It is also
the polar opposite of Pyongyang, North Korea _ the hub of a nation
where a preference of guns over butter has led to famine and
economic stagnation. In the wake of the historic summit between
North and South, other contrasts stand out. By SIG CHRISTENSON.
