<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
 CHRON   Taster's Choice  
 By Robin Davis  
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
 SAN FRANCISCO  _ Hot weather means cold drinks, so we had today's
panel taste seven different lemon-lime sodas.
<TEXT>
<P>
   We limited the tasting to those specifically flavored with lemon
and lime, because many sodas described as citrus are predominantly
grapefruit. The sodas were tasted just slightly chilled so the
flavor could come through.
</P>
<P>
   One brand scored marginally higher than the others, but many
sodas scored well. However, one panelist noted that in general none
of the sodas had much lemon-lime flavor, but rather tasted more
like carbonated sugar water.
</P>
<P>
   Panelists voted  &UR; 7-Up &LR;  (2 liters, $1.59 at many supermarkets)
tops, though not all considered it their favorite. Two panelists
liked the fizziness and found the flavor refreshing. One thought it
would be particularly refreshing served over ice. But others
thought it was thin and watery, and another detected a strange
aftertaste. Four would buy it; one might buy it.
</P>
<P>
   Second place was a tie between  &UR; Safeway &LR;  (2 liters, $1.29 at
Safeway) and  &UR; Sprite &LR;  (2 liters, $1.59 at many supermarkets). Those
who didn't care for Safeway seemed to like Sprite, and vice versa.
</P>
<P>
   Two panelists thought the Safeway soda was nicely balanced, but
others found it too sweet. One described it as ``cloying'' and
another thought it lacked lemon-lime characteristics. Three would
buy it; two would not.
</P>
<P>
   Some tasters thought Sprite was too sweet and lacked citrus
flavor, while others found it well balanced. Three would buy it,
one might buy it and one would not.
</P>
<P>
   Fourth place went to  &UR; Storm &LR;  (2 liters, $1.59 at many
supermarkets), made by Pepsi-Cola Bottling Co. and a relative
newcomer to the market. Panelists found this soda sweeter than the
others, and some thought it wasn't fizzy enough. Two panelists also
noted a bitter aftertaste. Three might buy it and two would not.
</P>
<P>
   Panelists were divided on  &UR; Shasta &LR;  (2 liters, $1.09 at Cala),
which placed fifth. Some liked the citrus flavor and good bubbles.
But others thought it tasted too chemical and processed. Three
would buy it and two would not.
</P>
<P>
   The panel also tasted Albertson's and Santa Cruz but they scored
too low to rate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-21-00 2140EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
