Naturally, this entails climbing a ladder to get up to the roof.
Unfortunately, many do- it-yourselfers (and a lot of professionals)
take ladder safety for granted; as a result, more than 90,000
ladder-related accidents are reported each year. (Ed Lipinski/New
York Times Illustration)
