in my mind of what I wanted, so I designed it,'' says Ms. Woods. In
Emily Wood's loft, a table commands the space with authority, top,
because it was designed specifically for it. Bottom, a sideboard is
as neatly organized as it's contents. (Fred R. Conrad/The New York
Times)
