   (NYT21) NEW YORK -- June 21, 2000 -- UNIVERSAL-LESCURE -- The
new Vivendi Universal will quickly morph into a global media
company with a decidedly European accent. The $34 billion buyout by
Vivendi, the world's largest water treatment company, of Seagram
Co. Ltd., one of the world's biggest spirits purveyors, will
necessitate some asset shedding, but Universal's key media and
entertainment executives have long-term contracts, so layoffs at
this level are not likely. Pierre Lescure, chief executive officer
of Paris-based entertainment company Canal Plus in which Vivendi is
half-owner, seen here at the announcement of the merger in New
York, will be responsible for all filmed entertainment assets,
including Universal Studios. (Ruby Washington/The New York Times)
