   (NYT906) NATCHITOCHES, La. -- June 21, 2000 -- RACE-PLANTATION-6
-- Betty Hertzog is descended from the slave-owning family that
built the Magnolia Plantation's original house, which burned in the
Civil War. Though the work buildings and cabins are now on National
Park Service land, the house belongs to Hertzog, who gives her own
tours of it. (Fred R. Conrad/The New York Times)
