<SLUG> BC-BBN-ASTROS-TRADE-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Alou, Lima interest Yankees
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By JOSEPH DUARTE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 2000, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
The New York Yankees have expressed interest in a possible deal to
acquire Astros outfielder Moises Alou and starting pitcher Jose
Lima.
</P>
<P>
   General manager Gerry Hunsicker declined Wednesday to discuss
specific trade rumors or players involved but said he is not
surprised by the speculation.
</P>
<P>
   The trade deadline is July 31.
</P>
<P>
   ``Any time you have a team in last place like we are approaching
the halfway point, there's going to be a lot of speculation
regarding your veteran players,'' Hunsicker said before Wednesday's
game with the Dodgers. ``So I'm not surprised.''
</P>
<P>
   Following three NL Central titles, the Astros have been a major
disappointment with the worst record in the majors through nearly
three months.
</P>
<P>
   Among the Yankees being mentioned in a deal for Alou and Lima
are outfielder Ricky Ledee, top infield prospect Alfonso Soriano
and a minor-league pitching prospect.
</P>
<P>
   Alou, who has one year remaining on a five-year contract worth a
little more than $25 million, has a no-trade clause in his
contract.
</P>
<P>
   ```It's the first time in my career that my name has been
mentioned in trade rumors during the season,'' said Alou.
</P>
<P>
   ``Rumors are just rumors. Usually, I am asked if I'd agree to go
to this place or that place, and that hasn't happened here. I have
a no-trade agreement. If I don't want to go anywhere, I won't.''
</P>
<P>
   Hunsicker would not say whether he has approached Alou about
waiving his no-trade clause.
</P>
<P>
   ``Unless he changes his mind in regard to being traded, that's a
moot point,'' Hunsicker said.
</P>
<P>
   Lima has been one of the team's biggest disappointments
following a 21-win season a year ago. He is 1-10 with a 7.07 ERA
but has pitched well in his last two starts.
</P>
<P>
   ``My sister called me from the Dominican and said she heard it
on the radio,'' Lima said. ``I guess I'd say I'm shocked. I hope it
doesn't happen. I have my family here and a home here. But if it
does, then I am a baseball player and I will do my job.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Hunsicker: ``It would be somewhat impractical for me to
think about trading starting pitching when it's so scarce.''
</P>
<P>
   The Yankees reportedly have been making a push to acquire
Chicago Cubs outfielder Sammy Sosa or Detroit outfielder Juan
Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
   The Boston Red Sox also have expressed interest recently in
Alou.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
