<HEADLINE>
UGLY DOG REPEATS AS FAIR CHAMP 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By GUY KOVNER   
 The Press Democrat, Santa Rosa, Calif.   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTA ROSA, Calif. _ Cisco Systems, one of the world's most
valuable companies, now has another feather _ or perhaps one should
say dog hair _ in its corporate cap.
</P>
<P>
   Nana, the world's ugliest dog, ``works'' at Cisco's Petaluma
office, where canines mix with the high-pressure Telecom Valley
work ethic.
</P>
<P>
   Yvonne Morones of Santa Rosa, an administrative assistant at
Cisco, shares her cubicle with Nana, a 17-year-old part Chihuahua,
part question mark.
</P>
<P>
   ``We call her a canardly,'' Morones said. As in ``canardly tell
what she is.''
</P>
<P>
   Judges at the Sonoma-Marin Fair World's Ugliest Dog Contest know
Nana as their favorite. Three times in the last five years,
including last year and again last Friday night, Nana has been
named world's ugliest dog.
</P>
<P>
   Not bad for an elderly pooch plucked off the streets as a stray
and adopted by Morones from an animal shelter.
</P>
<P>
   ``I fell in love with her,'' Morones said. ``I already had four
Chihuahuas.''
</P>
<P>
   Nana and her owner were invited onto the Tonight Show, starring
Jay Leno, after winning the homely hound contest last year. Apart
from a local TV appearance and a newspaper interview, no media
offers have come so far this summer.
</P>
<P>
   (The Press Democrat in Santa Rosa, Calif., is part of the New
York Times Regional Newspaper Group.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
